children.subject: Data 100 is fairly straight forward - watch lectures, understand what is happening, do the labs/hw - I would say that it is around 5-6 hours per week max

Everything you learn in 16A should be fine for 126. If you're not great at the probability I'd be very careful, since the course really builds on everything you learned in 70 and the first couple weeks go through the entirety of probability from 70 with some extra concepts and difficult problems. You'd probably want to review probability significantly before enrolling, and maybe consider taking a look at the homework posted on the website for this semester to see what the difficulty is like.

Just 61B + 126 does sounds like a doable schedule for sure, I haven't taken Data 100 so I can't comment on how much more that would add.
